Q1
Create an Employee Entity which contains the following fields: Name, Id, Age, Location
Q2)
Set up EmployeeRepository with Spring Data JPA
Q3)
Perform Create Operation on Entity using Spring Data JPA
Q4)
Perform Update Operation on Entity using Spring Data JPA
Q5)
Perform Delete Operation on Entity using Spring Data JPA
Q6)
Perform Read Operation on Entity using Spring Data JPA
Q7)
Get the total count of the number of Employees
Q8)
Implement Pagination and Sorting on the basis of Employee Age
Q9)
Create and use finder to find Employee by Name
Q10)
Create and use finder to find Employees starting with A character
Q11)
Create and use finder to find Employees Between the age of 28 to 32


Q1) Create an Employee Entity

Instructions

Create a package named entity.

Create a class Employee inside this package.

Define fields: id, name, age, location.

Mark this class as a database entity.

Configure id as the primary key.

Keep this class only for data representation (no logic).

Q2) Set up EmployeeRepository with Spring Data JPA

Instructions

Create a package named repository.

Create an interface EmployeeRepository.

Extend Spring Data JPA repository interface.

Link the repository with the Employee entity.

Do not add business logic here.

Q3) Perform Create Operation on Entity

Instructions

Create a package named service.

Create an interface EmployeeService.

Create service.impl package and implementation class.

Add a method in service for saving employee.

Call repository save method from service.

Create controller package.

Create EmployeeController.

Expose a POST API to create employee.

Controller must call service layer only.

Q4) Perform Update Operation on Entity

Instructions

Add update method in EmployeeService.

Implement update logic in service implementation.

Use repository to update employee data.

Expose a PUT API in EmployeeController.

Validate employee existence before update.

Q5) Perform Delete Operation on Entity

Instructions

Add delete method in EmployeeService.

Use repository delete functionality.

Expose DELETE API in controller.

Delete employee using employee id.

Handle case when employee does not exist.

Q6) Perform Read Operation on Entity

Instructions

Add read methods in service:

Get all employees

Get employee by id

Use repository find methods.

Expose GET APIs in controller.

Return list or single employee accordingly.

Q7) Get Total Count of Employees

Instructions

Use count functionality of repository.

Add count method in service.

Expose GET API to return total employee count.

Keep logic inside service layer.

Q8) Implement Pagination and Sorting by Age

Instructions

Use Spring Data pagination support in repository.

Add service method accepting page number and size.

Apply sorting based on employee age.

Expose GET API with pagination parameters.

Do not handle pagination logic in controller.

Q9) Finder: Find Employee by Name

Instructions

Define finder method in repository based on name.

Add corresponding service method.

Expose GET API in controller.

Pass name as request parameter or path variable.

Q10) Finder: Find Employees Starting with Character ‘A’

Instructions

Create finder method in repository for name starting with character.

Add service method calling repository finder.

Expose GET API in controller.

Allow passing starting character dynamically.

Q11) Finder: Find Employees Between Age 28 to 32

Instructions

Create finder method in repository for age range.

Add service method for age-between logic.

Expose GET API in controller.

Accept minimum and maximum age as inputs.